################  reference

####  commands (selected)

https://minecraft.gamepedia.com/Commands#Summary_of_commands

/blockdata	Modifies the data tag of a block.
/clear		Clears items from player inventory.
/clone		Copies blocks from one place to another.
/difficulty	Sets the difficulty level.
/effect		Add or remove status effects.
/enchant	Enchants a player item.
/entitydata	Modifies the data tag of an entity.
/execute	Executes another command.
/fill		Fills a region with a specific block.
/gamemode	Sets a player's game mode.
/gamerule	Sets or queries a game rule value.
/give		Gives an item to a player.
/list		Lists players on the server.
/locate		Locates closest structure.
/op		Grants operator status to a player.
/particle	Creates particles.
/playsound	Plays a sound.
/replaceitem	Replaces items in inventories.
/save-all	Saves the server to disk.
/save-off	Disables automatic server saves.
/save-on	Enables automatic server saves.
/say		Displays a message to multiple players.
/scoreboard	Manages objectives, players, teams, and tags.
/seed		Displays the world seed.
/setblock	Changes a block to another block.
/stop		Stops a server.
/stopsound	Stops a sound.
/summon		Summons an entity.
/teleport	Teleports entities, relative to the command's execution.
/tell		Displays a private message to other players.
/tellraw	Displays a JSON message to players.
/testfor	Counts entities matching specified conditions.
/testforblock	Tests whether a block is in a location.
/testforblocks	Tests whether the blocks in two regions match.
/tickingarea	Add, remove, or list ticking areas.
/time		Changes or queries the world's game time.
/tp		Teleports entities, relative to the teleported targets.
/weather	Sets the weather.
/xp		Adds or removes player experience.
/worldborder	Manages the world border.


####  target selectors

https://minecraft.gamepedia.com/Commands#Target_selectors

@<variable>[<argument>=<value>,<argument>=<value>, ...]

-- can use '!' in front of the value to negate its meaning

@p	nearest player
@r	random player
@a	all players
@e	all entities
@s	the entity executing the command

arguments	value meaning
---------	-------------
x, y, z		coordinate
r, rm		radius (max, min)
dx, dy, dz	volume dimensions
c		count
type		entity type
name		entity name
l, lm		experience level (max, min)
m		game mode
rx, rxm		vertical rotation (max, min)
ry, rym		horizontal rotation (max, min)
score_name	max score
score_name_min	min score
tag		scoreboard tag
team		team name


####  /effect

https://minecraft.gamepedia.com/Status_effect

effect <player> clear (removes all effects)
effect <player> <effect> [seconds] [amplifier] [hideParticles]
effect clear <entity> [<effect>]                                                         [upcoming 1.13]
effect give <entity> <effect> [<seconds>] [<amplifier>] [<hideParticles>]                [upcoming 1.13]

<player> is a name or target-selector
<effect> is an id or name
<amplifier> is 0 for level I, etc.                     max 255, but 128 to 255 are treated as −128 to −1

1	Speed		Increases walking speed                                inc speed, 20% * level; too high outpaces chunk loading
2	Slowness	Decreases walking speed
3	Haste		Increases mining and attack speed
4	Mining Fatigue	Decreases mining and attack speed
5	Strength	Increases melee damage                                 inc melee damage, 3 * level
6	Instant Health	Heals entities, damages undead                         heals damage, 2 * 2^level
7	Instant Damage	Damages entities, heals undead
8	Jump Boost	Increases jump height and reduces fall damage          useful up to level 15
9	Nausea		Wobbles and warps the screen
10	Regeneration	Regenerates health over time                           useful up to level 6
11	Resistance	Reduces most damage
12	Fire Resistance	Immunity to fire, etc.
13	Water Breathing	Prevents drowning                                      useful up to level 3
14	Invisibility	Grants invisibility                                    on / off
15	Blindness 	Impairs vision and disables the ability to sprint
16	Night Vision	Negates darkness                                       on / off
17	Hunger		Increases food exhaustion
18	Weakness	Decreases melee damage
19	Poison		Inflicts damage over time (but can't kill)
20	Wither		Inflicts damage over time (can kill)
21	Health Boost 	Increases maximum health
22	Absorption	Adds damage absorption                                 absorb damage, 4 * level
23	Saturation 	Restores hunger and saturation                         restores hunger,  1 * level
24	Glowing 	Outlines entities (can be seen through blocks)
25	Levitation	Floats entities upwards
26	Luck 		Increases chances of high-quality loot
27	Bad Luck 	Reduces chances of high-quality loot


####  /execute

execute <entity> <x> <y> <z> <command ...>    -or-
execute <entity> <x> <y> <z> detect <x2> <y2> <z2> <block> <dataValue|state> <command ...>

the second form only executes the command if the <block> at <x2> <y2> <z2> has the specified <dataValue|state>

<block> is the block id; e.g. minecraft:stone  (ID values might work as well ...)
<dataValue> is a valid block data for that type of block or -1 to match any block data
<state> is valid block state for that type of block or * to match any block state


